# IPC Error Message Extraction

super-ipc wraps backend errors as `AppError('error', { inner })`, so `error.message` is always the literal string `"error"`. Use the `getIpcErrorMessage` helper to extract the real message.

```typescript
import { getIpcErrorMessage } from '../../../utils/warningDetectors';

// ❌ BAD — always shows "error"
catch (error: any) {
  addAlert(`Operation failed: ${error.message}`, 'error');
}

// ✅ GOOD — extracts inner.message
catch (error: any) {
  addAlert(`Operation failed: ${getIpcErrorMessage(error)}`, 'error');
}
```
